claim.claim-text:
1. A sample holder system for a charged particle beam system having a sample chamber with a sample stage, comprising:
a stage mount for being affixed to the stage of a charged particle beam system, the stage mount including three alignment structures;
a base plate including three alignment structures, each alignment structure on the base plate structured to mate with a corresponding alignment structure on the stage mount, one of each mating alignment structures on the base plate or on stage mount including a hemispherical portion;
a sample tray configured to be removably attachable onto the base plate, the sample tray having multiple holes for positioning sample blocks;
a clamp holding the sample tray to the base plate;
a calibration standard holder secured to the stage mount and remaining on the stage mount as samples are changed in the charged particle beam system; and
springs positioned on the base plate to press the sample blocks into the sample tray and to repeatably orient the sample blocks relative to the sample tray.

6. A sample holder system for a charged particle beam system having a sample chamber with a sample stage, comprising
a stage mount for being affixed to the stage of a charged particle beam system, the stage mount including three alignment structures;
a base plate including three alignment structures, each alignment structure on the base plate structured to mate with a corresponding alignment structure on the stage mount, one of each mating alignment structures on the base plate or on stage mount including a hemispherical portion;
a sample tray configured to be removably attachable onto the base plate, the sample tray having multiple holes for positioning sample blocks;
a clamp holding the sample tray to the base plate;
a calibration standard holder secured to the stage mount and remaining on the stage mount as samples are changed in the charged particle beam system; and
springs positioned on the stage mount to ensure electrical contact between the stage mount and the base plate, the springs providing sufficient biasing force to provide electrical contact while still allowing the weight of the sample tray, base plate, and sample blocks to cause the aligning structures to fully engage.

11. A sample holder system for a charged particle beam system having a sample chamber with a sample stage, comprising:
a stage mount for being affixed to the stage of a charged particle beam system, the stage mount including three alignment structures;
a base plate including three alignment structures, each alignment structure on the base plate structured to mate with a corresponding alignment structure on the stage mount;
a sample tray configured to be removably attachable onto the base plate, the sample tray having multiple sample blocks positions;
a calibration standard holder secured to the stage mount and remaining on the stage mount as samples are changed in the charged particle beam system; and
springs positioned on the base plate to press the sample blocks into the sample tray and to repeatably position the sample blocks relative to the sample tray.

16. A sample holder system for a charged particle beam system having a sample chamber with a sample stage, comprising:
a stage mount for being affixed to the stage of a charged particle beam system, the stage mount including three alignment structures;
a base plate including three alignment structures, each alignment structure on the base plate structured to mate with a corresponding alignment structure on the stage mount;
a sample tray configured to be removably attachable onto the base plate, the sample tray having multiple sample blocks positions;
a calibration standard holder secured to the stage mount and remaining on the stage mount as samples are changed in the charged particle beam system; and
springs positioned on the stage mount to ensure electrical contact between the stage mount and the base plate, the springs providing sufficient biasing force to provide electrical contact while still allowing the weight of the sample tray, base plate, and sample blocks to cause the aligning structures to fully engage.
